  "metadata": {
    "title": "CVE-2018-20815 QEMU: device_tree: heap buffer overflow while loading device tree blob (important)",
    "reference": [
      {
        "ref_id": "CVE-2018-20815",
        "ref_url": "https://access.redhat.com/security/cve/CVE-2018-20815",
        "source": "CVE"
      }
    ],
    "description": "DOCUMENTATION: A heap buffer overflow issue was found in the load_device_tree() function of QEMU, which is invoked to load a device tree blob at boot time. It occurs due to device tree size manipulation before buffer allocation, which could overflow a signed int type. A user/process could use this flaw to potentially execute arbitrary code on a host system with privileges of the QEMU process.",
